  "texts": [
    "To obtain detailed information for each collected PMID, we created another function, fetch_records_for_ids, which fetched the complete records from the Entrez API.",
    "We modified this function to also attempt to retrieve PubMed Central IDs (PMCIDs) for each article, as these IDs are often required to access the full text of the articles.",
    "The function extracted various data fields from the retrieved records, including PMID, PM-CID (if available), article title, abstract, authors, journal, and publication date.",
    "The actual fields retrieved can vary depending on the availability of metadata for each article.",
    "To ensure the stability of the data collection process and respect the rate limits of the Entrez API, we implemented batch processing, where IDs were fetched in batches of 100, with a 0.5-second pause between each batch."
  ],
